node.text:
I will never get tired of sharing Mary’s story. 💙 She’s a refugee from South Sudan, a powerful advocate for education, a TED speaker and a theatre student.

For #WorldRefugeeDay, please watch this film as she and I play a little game to talk about what home means to us - with some very special heirlooms - and why getting an education is so important for all refugees.

There’s so much I could say about this incredible woman - but she can tell you herself. Keep an eye on my Instagram Stories today where she’ll be showing you all a glimpse of her life in Minnesota, and her dreams and goals for the future. You can follow her at @marymaker_43 - and please head to @refugees to see and hear more incredible stories like hers. Thank you. 

#WithRefugees

node.text:
I am so honored and grateful to be named a United Nations Goodwill Ambassador for UNHCR, The UN Refugee Agency. 

The refugees I’ve met over the years have inspired me through their strength, resilience and incredible capabilities to teach and help support their communities.

I’m proud to support @refugees who work tirelessly every day to help ensure that the millions of people who have been forced to flee their homes, leaving behind all they’ve known or had... are able to live in safety and with dignity. Please join me on this journey and give them hope. Link in my bio. 

#WithRefugees

node.text: Rita is the first refugee yoga teacher in Kenya’s Kakuma camp. She’s using the power of yoga to bring wellness and healing to both refugees and humanitarian workers with her classes – now online because of COVID-19 restrictions. Rita’s practice focuses on messages of self-acceptance and mental well-being. On this #WorldMentalHealthDay we all must realize that mental health support should be a right, not a luxury, for @refugees, the humanitarians supporting them, and everyone else. #WithRefugees 🙏🏽❤️ @refugees

node.text:
When I saw this video that @refugees just posted I wanted to share it with you guys as quickly as possible (thanks @danamhughes 🙏🏽🙌🏽). Uganda has a history of being kind to refugees. I witnessed it firsthand when I visited a @refugees camp last year.

This week Uganda opened up its borders to thousands of desperate refugees seeking a safe haven after fleeing horrific violence in the Democratic Republic of Congo. Mostly women and children had been stranded in a remote, inaccessible area, living for weeks without food or water.
 
Uganda is a great example to the world, showing how even during #COVID19 we can still find ways to safely welcome those in need.  Thankful for @refugees staff like @duniyaakhan who are there on the frontlines working with governments and supporting the many people who still have no choice but to flee their homes, even in this challenging time. 

If you guys can donate, even one dollar, the link is in my bio. 

#WithRefugees #EveryActionCounts #Uganda

node.text:
After we had to push our original premiere date we are finally hitting theaters July 31!! So proud of this movie! One of the illest projects I’ve ever done in my life, and coming at a time where untold stories are finally being brought to light. Directed by King @RZA 💥

@kyletekiela @ctcmovie @shameikmoore @dshippjr @blackmouf @eizagonzalez @theterrencehoward @ethanhawke @realwesleysnipes @rumbleriot @wellgousa LET’S GO!!! The distributors have committed to donating a portion of the film’s proceeds to lowernine.org, a nonprofit organization dedicated to the long-term recovery of New Orleans’ historic Lower Ninth Ward. 🙌🏽 Original song by @wutangclan #CutThroatCity

node.text: Life was so tough for the Syrian refugee families I met when I visited the camp in Jordan in 2014, so I could not imagine how much harder COVID-19 has made their lives. That’s why ahead of #WorldRefugee Day I connected with Irene, the camp manager for Za’atari, which now houses nearly 80,000 refugees. This inspiring woman is truly committed to working for and standing with @refugees, even in the face of a global pandemic. After learning three months ago that that Za’atari was going to be locked down due to coronavirus, Irene packed a bag and moved to the camp. She wanted to make sure she could stay close to the refugees she serves. Irene is the true definition of a humanitarian. But you don’t have to work at UNHCR or be a hero to stand in solidarity with refugees. Everyone can help make a difference. Every action counts. Please watch and click the link in my bio to find out more. #RefugeeDay #WithRefugees

node.title: Meet UNHCR's Irene Omondi - World Refugee Day

node.text: I produced this PSA 2 years ago for #BlackLivesMatter with @dijonnaise911 who directed it, and it’s heartbreaking to know that it’s more relevant now than ever. Sending love and power to the families and loved ones of #GeorgeFloyd #BreonnaTaylor #AhmaudArbery and all those that we might not know but still fight for. Justice needs to be served. “Injustice anywhere is a threat to justice everywhere. We are caught in an inescapable network of mutuality, tied in a single garment of destiny. Whatever affects one directly, affects all indirectly.” - Martin Luther King Jr.

#ad For full Product Information, including Boxed Warning, and Patient Information for Lo Loestrin® Fe (norethindrone acetate & ethinyl estradiol tablets, ethinyl estradiol tablets & ferrous fumarate tablets), see @loloestrinfepi.

Did you know that World Sexual Health Day (WSHD) happens every September? My health is super important to me, but WSHD made me think hard about my reproductive health specifically. I’ve partnered with AbbVie, the maker of Lo Loestrin Fe, to encourage women everywhere to prioritize knowing their options when it comes to pregnancy prevention. I’m excited to start the conversation about women’s reproductive health with all of you! Knowledge is power, and it’s up to us to make sure we are informed about our choices – especially because the right option for you might be different than the right option for someone else. Check out @loloestrinferx for information about contraception.

Lo Loestrin Fe is a prescription birth control pill used for the prevention of pregnancy. If you are moderately obese, discuss with your healthcare provider whether Lo Loestrin Fe is appropriate for you.

There are serious risks with birth control pills, like Lo Loestrin Fe, including blood clots, stroke and heart attack, which can be fatal. Do not take Lo Loestrin Fe if you’ve had any of these conditions. Lo Loestrin Fe users should not smoke as smoking increases these risks, especially if you are over 35 years old. Do not take Lo Loestrin Fe if you have high blood pressure that medicine can’t control, certain cancers, liver disease, unexplained vaginal bleeding, are taking Hepatitis C drugs, or if you could be pregnant. The Pill does not protect against HIV or sexually transmitted diseases.

#worldsexualhealthday #birthcontrol #womenshealth #thepill #contraceptive #oralcontraceptive #pregnancyprevention

node.text:
This art represents the complexity of the infinite of self. On one side of the card you are just like everyone else. On the other side you might be a Queen, a Joker, an Ace… you never know which card you’re going to pick or how the game is gonna change based on your choices. The two versions represent our duality and the way that good and bad can co exist within each other to create your most powerful self. That is Toro Gato.

#ToroGato Part I is officially out #LinkInBio ♾🫀🖤🃏

node.text:
Toro Gato Part I is officially out!!!!!!!!!!!!

Thank you to my incredible fans for joining me in such a wild journey. This has been a 5 year road of creation, anticipation, frustration, laughter, blood, sweat and tears. It is an honor for me to share my art with you whenever I get the privilege to. I love you guys so much. 

@bigjeeve thank you for sitting next to me as we pooled thru hundreds of sounds and the endless hours of tweaking and mixing, recutting and mixing again you spent by my side. 

Thank you @ale_ssiofilippelli for all of the nights you stayed up working on designs and facing your nightmares. It has been a thrilling and emotional journey. Watching you grow into the insanely talented artist you are has been so powerful for me. Thank you for all the 😵‍💫❤️‍🩹 and the ❤️‍🔥🙏🏽🤦🏽‍♀️🤯🌦 and the 🗝📦❣️🇮🇹 🌶🌈♟. I love you. My friend. My friend. My friend. 

Thank you @roi33 Kazual @davidblaine @michaeldoi @alissahmusic @haroldjulian @polisg @valerie_von_sobel @alionakononova @robearhair @iamdevapink @mmsanett Jai Shukla @_pwnisher_ @peterfrance and the whole crew in production and post for sharing your talent with me. 

Thank you Josh, Nicole and Michelle at @yellowheartNFT for believing and moving with passion. Thank you to the entire YH team for your hard work in the NFT space. As artists we are often overlooked and underpaid. Thank you for never failing to see the value in us.

Thank you to my new tribe @juriel___ @kevinderoos_ @hybridmovementcompany @bodymechanicnyc for bringing so much soul and love to this. Ready to build our tour!!

Thank you keithgrossman for pushing me against my own comforts. You are a brilliant loving funny wildly intelligent leader that I will always follow fiercely. 

And my love @dijonnaise911 Thank you for your insanely good eye and sharing this life with me. I love you my bull. You inspire me. Always. 

-Toro Gato.
#LinkInBio 🫀🖤

From the live string quartets paired with the haunting and fearless raw visuals, Graham plants flag this new unchartered territory. node.text:
Within you is a world. It sits across a dinner table from your heartbroken lover. It is watching you as your greatest enemy cradles you as you take your last breath. It reflects behind your glasses, and watches as you paint a picture. It whispers in your ear behind every note you sing, and waits in the rain for you to open the door. It haunts you in your dreams and celebrates you when you wake. Our shadow self is here… her name Toro Gato. Let us pray to become ourselves in totality.

From Alessio: Creating the graphics for Toro Gato, has always felt like something bigger and deeper than just this. It was about diving into the visuals and the universe of Toro Gato, and becoming one with it. 
These two graphics represent the duality of Toro Gato, like a panther that looks docile but can turn into a wild and strong spirit. Or a candid element like a church, that can be the “gato” side, that feels like a mixing controversial scenario considering the darkness in “toro” but in which both can live and exist. All of these, represent the controversy of this character and the darkness but also the mysterious personality. With each art, through the artistic eye of Toro Gato, we bring to life everything that went through creating and the artistic process behind this project, like a puzzle, each art is unique, and gives a sense to what’s coming next. 

Toro Gato drops in 4 days… who’s ready? 🫀🖤

node.text:
Toro Gato represents the hidden parts of you. There is a part of you that you present to the world, and a part of you that you hide from it. Who are you on stage when the curtain is closed? Are you holding your own strings, or allowing yourself to be manipulated for validation? Are you 1000% yourself in truth, or are you presenting your representative? So many of us are on stage and we don’t even realize it. Are you even you at all?

Countdown to showtime... ♾ days 🫀🖤
